keyword.description:
A keyword or tag describing a resource.
[CIM context:
The intended content type of the model, usually the profile keyword. Used to identify what profiles and content is expected in the document, e.g., Equipment, Boundary, SSH, AE, etc. The same keyword is used for different versions of same profile. It can be also used to identify different content based on the same profile.
For instance, as the equipment profile can be used for both boundary data and equipment not related to boundary, the keyword is different to indicate that boundary data is exchanged. In order to avoid ambiguity the property is not exchanged in cases where the document contains multiple profiles referenced by dct:conformsTo.].

nextVersion.description: The next version for the resource.

previousVersion.description:
The previous version of a resource in a lineage.
This property is meant to be used to specify a version chain, consisting of snapshots of a resource.

The notion of version used by this property is limited to versions resulting from revisions occurring to a resource as part of its life-cycle. One of the typical cases here is representing the history of the versions of a dataset that have been released over time.

startDate.description:
This property contains the start of the 
period.
[CIM context:
The date and time that this model represents, i.e. for which the model is (or was) valid. It indicates the beginning of the validity period. It is indicating either an instant (in cases where the model is only valid for a point in time) or the start time of a period. If not provided the model is considered valid for any time stamp. The format is an extended format according to the ISO 8601-2005. European exchanges shall refer to UTC.].

Duration.description: Duration as "PnYnMnDTnHnMnS" which conforms to ISO 8601, where nY expresses a number of years, nM a number of months, nD a number of days. The letter T separates the date expression from the time expression and, after it, nH identifies a number of hours, nM a number of minutes and nS a number of seconds. The number of seconds could be expressed as a decimal number, but all other numbers are integers.

temporalResolution.description:
Minimum time period resolvable in the dataset.
[CIM context: 

Describes the Market Time Unit (MTU), e.g. hourly, 15 min., etc.]

version.description: The version number of a resource.

generatedAtTime.description:
Generation is the completion of production of a new entity by an activity. This entity did not exist before generation and becomes available for usage after this generation.
[CIM context:
The date and time when the model was serialized in the document where the header is located. The format is an extended format according to the ISO 8601-2005. European exchanges shall refer to UTC.].

wasGeneratedBy.description:
Generation is the completion of production of a new entity by an activity. This entity did not exist before generation and becomes available for usage after this generation.
[CIM context:
Reference to an activity or the exact business nature (process, configuration) which produced or uses the model.].

Model.applicationSoftware.description:
Identifies the application software which generated this instance file. The application software term is defined in ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765:2017. The application software can be identified either:
- as a string which contains information on the software name and version, e.g. <tool_name>-<major_version>.<minor_version>.<patch>, or
- as a reference to a software identification tag as defined by ISO/IEC 19770-2:2015 and ISO/IEC/IEEE 24765:2017.

processType.description: The exact business nature. Reference to Business Process configurations.

usedSettings.description: Reference to a set of parameters describing used settings (e.g. power flow settings, process settings, etc.) applied to the model prior its serialisation.

alternativeVersionOf.description:
This resource is an alternative version of a non-versioned or abstract resource.
This property is intended for relating a versioned resource to a non-versioned or abstract resource at the same time express that multiple versions exist.
dcat-cim:alternativeVersionOf is a specialisation of dcat:isVersionOf with the restriction that the resource shall have a preferred version (dcat-cim:preferredVersion) so that the preferred dataset can be used when there is no need to access all alternative versions.

preferredVersion.description:
The preferred version of a resource in a lineage of alternative versions.
This property is used to specify a specific version to be the preference in a chain of alternatives, consisting of snapshots of a resource.

FullModel.description: It represents the full model header and its contents is described by the Model class.

RotatingMachineDynamics.damping.description: Damping torque coefficient (D) (>= 0). A proportionality constant that, when multiplied by the angular velocity of the rotor poles with respect to the magnetic field (frequency), results in the damping torque. This value is often zero when the sources of damping torques (generator damper windings, load damping effects, etc.) are modelled in detail. Typical value = 0.

RotatingMachineDynamics.inertia.description: Inertia constant of generator or motor and mechanical load (H) (> 0). This is the specification for the stored energy in the rotating mass when operating at rated speed. For a generator, this includes the generator plus all other elements (turbine, exciter) on the same shaft and has units of MW x s. For a motor, it includes the motor plus its mechanical load. Conventional units are PU on the generator MVA base, usually expressed as MW x s / MVA or just s. This value is used in the accelerating power reference frame for operator training simulator solutions. Typical value = 3.

RotatingMachineDynamics.saturationFactor.description: Saturation factor at rated terminal voltage (S1) (>= 0). Not used by simplified model. Defined by defined by S(E1) in the SynchronousMachineSaturationParameters diagram. Typical value = 0,02.

SynchronousMachineDetailed.efdBaseRatio.description: Ratio (exciter voltage/generator voltage) of Efd bases of exciter and generator models (> 0). Typical value = 1.

SynchronousMachineDetailed.ifdBaseType.description: Excitation base system mode. It should be equal to the value of WLMDV given by the user. WLMDV is the PU ratio between the field voltage and the excitation current: Efd = WLMDV x Ifd. Typical value = ifag.

SynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance..description: Saturation loading correction factor (Ks) (>= 0). Used only by type J model. Typical value = 0.

SynchronousMachineModelKind.subtransient.description: WECC type F variant of subtransient synchronous machine model.
WECC type J variant of subtransient synchronous machine model.

RotorKind.roundRotor.description: Round rotor type of synchronous machine.

RotorKind.salientPole.description: Salient pole type of synchronous machine.

SynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance..description: Type of rotor on physical machine.
Damping time constant for “Canay” reactance (>= 0).  Typical value = 0.
Direct-axis transient rotor time constant (T'do) (> SynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance.tppdo). Typical value = 5.
Direct-axis subtransient rotor time constant (T''do) (> 0). Typical value = 0,03.
Quadrature-axis subtransient rotor time constant (T''qo) (> 0). Typical value = 0,03.
Quadrature-axis transient rotor time constant (T'qo) (> SynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance.tppqo). Typical value = 0,5.

Direct-axis synchronous reactance (Xd) (>= SynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance.xDirectTrans). The quotient of a sustained value of that AC component of armature voltage that is produced by the total direct-axis flux due to direct-axis armature current and the value of the AC component of this current, the machine running at rated speed. Typical value = 1,8.

Quadrature-axis synchronous reactance (Xq) (>= SynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance.xQuadTrans). The ratio of the component of reactive armature voltage, due to the quadrature-axis component of armature current, to this component of current, under steady state conditions and at rated frequency. Typical value = 1,6.

SynchronousMachineEquivalentCircuit.description: The electrical equations for all variations of the synchronous models are based on the SynchronousEquivalentCircuit diagram for the direct- and quadrature- axes. Equations for conversion between equivalent circuit and time constant reactance forms: Xd = Xad + Xl X’d = Xl + Xad x Xfd / (Xad + Xfd) X”d = Xl + Xad x Xfd x X1d / (Xad x Xfd + Xad x X1d + Xfd x X1d) Xq = Xaq + Xl X’q = Xl + Xaq x X1q / (Xaq + X1q) X”q = Xl + Xaq x X1q x X2q / (Xaq x X1q + Xaq x X2q + X1q x X2q) T’do = (Xad + Xfd) / (omega0 x Rfd) T”do = (Xad x Xfd + Xad x X1d + Xfd x X1d) / (omega0 x R1d x (Xad + Xfd) T’qo = (Xaq + X1q) / (omega0 x R1q) T”qo = (Xaq x X1q + Xaq x X2q + X1q x X2q) / (omega0 x R2q x (Xaq + X1q) Same equations using CIM attributes from SynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance class on left of "=" and SynchronousMachineEquivalentCircuit class on right (except as noted): xDirectSync = xad + RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance xDirectTrans = RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance + xad x xfd / (xad + xfd) xDirectSubtrans = RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance + xad x xfd x x1d / (xad x xfd + xad x x1d + xfd x x1d) xQuadSync = xaq + RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance xQuadTrans = RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance + xaq x x1q / (xaq+ x1q) xQuadSubtrans = RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance + xaq x x1q x x2q / (xaq x x1q + xaq x x2q + x1q x x2q) tpdo = (xad + xfd) / (2 x pi x nominal frequency x rfd) tppdo = (xad x xfd + xad x x1d + xfd x x1d) / (2 x pi x nominal frequency x r1d x (xad + xfd) tpqo = (xaq + x1q) / (2 x pi x nominal frequency x r1q) tppqo = (xaq x x1q + xaq x x2q + x1q x x2q) / (2 x pi x nominal frequency x r2q x (xaq + x1q) These are only valid for a simplified model where "Canay" reactance is zero.

AsynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance.description: Transient rotor time constant (T'o) (> AsynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance.tppo). Typical value = 5.
Subtransient rotor time constant (T''o) (> 0). Typical value = 0,03.

AsynchronousMachineEquivalentCircuit.description: The electrical equations of all variations of the asynchronous model are based on the AsynchronousEquivalentCircuit diagram for the direct- and quadrature- axes, with two equivalent rotor windings in each axis. Equations for conversion between equivalent circuit and time constant reactance forms: Xs = Xm + Xl X' = Xl + Xm x Xlr1 / (Xm + Xlr1) X'' = Xl + Xm x Xlr1 x Xlr2 / (Xm x Xlr1 + Xm x Xlr2 + Xlr1 x Xlr2) T'o = (Xm + Xlr1) / (omega0 x Rr1) T''o = (Xm x Xlr1 + Xm x Xlr2 + Xlr1 x Xlr2) / (omega0 x Rr2 x (Xm + Xlr1) Same equations using CIM attributes from AsynchronousMachineTimeConstantReactance class on left of "=" and AsynchronousMachineEquivalentCircuit class on right (except as noted): xs = xm + RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance xp = RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance + xm x xlr1 / (xm + xlr1) xpp = RotatingMachineDynamics.statorLeakageReactance + xm x xlr1 x xlr2 / (xm x xlr1 + xm x xlr2 + xlr1 x xlr2) tpo = (xm + xlr1) / (2 x pi x nominal frequency x rr1) tppo = (xm x xlr1 + xm x xlr2 + xlr1 x xlr2) / (2 x pi x nominal frequency x rr2 x (xm + xlr1).

GovCT1.description:
General model for any prime mover with a PID governor, used primarily for combustion turbine and combined cycle units. This model can be used to represent a variety of prime movers controlled by PID governors. It is suitable, for example, for the representation of:
  • gas turbine and single shaft combined cycle turbines
  • diesel engines with modern electronic or digital governors
  • steam turbines where steam is supplied from a large boiler drum or a large header whose pressure is substantially constant over the period under study
  • simple hydro turbines in dam configurations where the water column length is short and water inertia effects are minimal.
Additional information on this model is available in the 2012 IEEE report, Dynamic Models for Turbine-Governors in Power System Studies, 3.1.2.3 pages 3-4 (GGOV1).

GovCT1.aset.description: Acceleration limiter setpoint (Aset). Unit = PU / s. Typical value = 0,01.

GovCT1.db.description: Speed governor deadband in PU speed (db). In the majority of applications, it is recommended that this value be set to zero. Typical value = 0.

GovCT1.dm.description: Speed sensitivity coefficient (Dm). Dm can represent either the variation of the engine power with the shaft speed or the variation of maximum power capability with shaft speed. If it is positive it describes the falling slope of the engine speed verses power characteristic as speed increases. A slightly falling characteristic is typical for reciprocating engines and some aero-derivative turbines. If it is negative the engine power is assumed to be unaffected by the shaft speed, but the maximum permissible fuel flow is taken to fall with falling shaft speed. This is characteristic of single-shaft industrial turbines due to exhaust temperature limits. Typical value = 0.

GovCT1.kiload.description: Load limiter integral gain for PI controller (Kiload). Typical value = 0,67.

GovCT1.kimw.description: Power controller (reset) gain (Kimw). The default value of 0,01 corresponds to a reset time of 100 s. A value of 0,001 corresponds to a relatively slow-acting load controller. Typical value = 0,01.

GovCT1.kpload.description: Load limiter proportional gain for PI controller (Kpload). Typical value = 2.

GovCT1.ldref.description: Load limiter reference value (Ldref). Typical value = 1.

GovCT1.rdown.description: Maximum rate of load limit decrease (Rdown). Typical value = -99.

GovCT1.ropen.description: Maximum valve opening rate (Ropen). Unit = PU / s. Typical value = 0.10.

The type AC2A model is similar to that of type AC1A except for the inclusion of exciter time constant compensation and exciter field current limiting elements.

ExcIEEEAC3A.description: IEEE 421.5-2005 type AC3A model. The model represents the field-controlled alternator-rectifier excitation systems designated type AC3A. These excitation systems include an alternator main exciter with non-controlled rectifiers. The exciter employs self-excitation, and the voltage regulator power is derived from the exciter output voltage. Therefore, this system has an additional nonlinearity, simulated by the use of a multiplier whose inputs are the voltage regulator command signal, Va, and the exciter output voltage, Efd, times KR. This model is applicable to excitation systems employing static voltage regulators. Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 6.3.

ExcIEEEAC4A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type AC4A model. The model represents type AC4A alternator-supplied controlled-rectifier excitation system which is quite different from the other types of AC systems. This high initial response excitation system utilizes a full thyristor bridge in the exciter output circuit.  The voltage regulator controls the firing of the thyristor bridges. The exciter alternator uses an independent voltage regulator to control its output voltage to a constant value. These effects are not modelled; however, transient loading effects on the exciter alternator are included.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 6.4.

ExcIEEEAC5A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type AC5A model. The model represents a simplified model for brushless excitation systems. The regulator is supplied from a source, such as a permanent magnet generator, which is not affected by system disturbances.  Unlike other AC models, this model uses loaded rather than open circuit exciter saturation data in the same way as it is used for the DC models.  Because the model has been widely implemented by the industry, it is sometimes used to represent other types of systems when either detailed data for them are not available or simplified models are required.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 6.5.

ExcIEEEAC8B.description: IEEE 421.5-2005 type AC8B model. This model represents a PID voltage regulator with either a brushless exciter or DC exciter. The AVR in this model consists of PID control, with separate constants for the proportional (KPR), integral (KIR), and derivative (KDR) gains. The representation of the brushless exciter (TE, KE, SE, KC, KD) is similar to the model type AC2A. The type AC8B model can be used to represent static voltage regulators applied to brushless excitation systems. Digitally based voltage regulators feeding DC rotating main exciters can be represented with the AC type AC8B model with the parameters KC and KD set to 0. For thyristor power stages fed from the generator terminals, the limits VRMAX and VRMIN should be a function of terminal voltage: VT x VRMAX and VT x VRMIN. Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 6.8.

ExcIEEEDC1A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type DC1A model. This model represents field-controlled DC commutator exciters with continuously acting voltage regulators (especially the direct-acting rheostatic, rotating amplifier, and magnetic amplifier types).  Because this model has been widely implemented by the industry, it is sometimes used to represent other types of systems when detailed data for them are not available or when a simplified model is required.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 5.1.

ExcIEEEDC1A.efd1.description: Exciter voltage at which exciter saturation is defined (EFD1) (> 0). Typical value = 3,1.

ExcIEEEDC1A.efd2.description: Exciter voltage at which exciter saturation is defined (EFD2) (> 0). Typical value = 2,3.

ExcIEEEDC1A.exclim.description: (exclim). IEEE standard is ambiguous about lower limit on exciter output. true = a lower limit of zero is applied to integrator output false = a lower limit of zero is not applied to integrator output. Typical value = true.

ExcIEEEDC1A.ke.description: Exciter constant related to self-excited field (KE). Typical value = 0.

ExcIEEEDC1A.kf.description: Excitation control system stabilizer gain (KF) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.1.

ExcIEEEDC1A.seefd1.description: Exciter saturation function value at the corresponding exciter voltage, EFD1 (SE[EFD1]) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.33.

ExcIEEEDC1A.seefd2.description: Exciter saturation function value at the corresponding exciter voltage, EFD2 (SE[EFD2]) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,1.

ExcIEEEDC1A.ta.description: Voltage regulator time constant (TA) (> 0). Typical value = 0,06.

ExcIEEEDC1A.tb.description: Voltage regulator time constant (TB) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.

ExcIEEEDC1A.tc.description: Voltage regulator time constant (TC) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.

ExcIEEEDC1A.te.description: Exciter time constant, integration rate associated with exciter control (TE) (> 0). Typical value = 0,46.

ExcIEEEDC1A.tf.description: Excitation control system stabilizer time constant (TF) (> 0). Typical value = 1.

ExcIEEEDC1A.uelin.description: UEL input (uelin). true = input is connected to the HV gate false = input connects to the error signal. Typical value = true.

ExcIEEEDC1A.vrmax.description: Maximum voltage regulator output (VRMAX) (> ExcIEEEDC1A.vrmin). Typical value = 1.

ExcIEEEDC1A.vrmin.description: Minimum voltage regulator output (VRMIN) (< 0 and < ExcIEEEDC1A.vrmax). Typical value = -0,9.

ExcIEEEDC2A.description: IEEE 421.5-2005 type DC2A model. This model represents field-controlled DC commutator exciters with continuously acting voltage regulators having supplies obtained from the generator or auxiliary bus. It differs from the type DC1A model only in the voltage regulator output limits, which are now proportional to terminal voltage VT. It is representative of solid-state replacements for various forms of older mechanical and rotating amplifier regulating equipment connected to DC commutator exciters. Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 5.2.

ExcIEEEDC2A.efd1.description: Exciter voltage at which exciter saturation is defined (EFD1) (> 0). Typical value = 3,05.

ExcIEEEDC2A.efd2.description: Exciter voltage at which exciter saturation is defined (EFD2) (> 0). Typical value = 2,29.

ExcIEEEDC2A.exclim.description: (exclim). IEEE standard is ambiguous about lower limit on exciter output. Typical value = - 999 which means that there is no limit applied.

ExcIEEEDC2A.ke.description: Exciter constant related to self-excited field (KE). Typical value = 1.

ExcIEEEDC2A.kf.description: Excitation control system stabilizer gain (KF) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,1.

ExcIEEEDC2A.seefd1.description: Exciter saturation function value at the corresponding exciter voltage, EFD1 (SE[EFD1]) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,279.

ExcIEEEDC2A.seefd2.description: Exciter saturation function value at the corresponding exciter voltage, EFD2 (SE[EFD2]) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,117.

ExcIEEEDC2A.ta.description: Voltage regulator time constant (TA) (> 0). Typical value = 0,01.

ExcIEEEDC2A.tb.description: Voltage regulator time constant (TB) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.

ExcIEEEDC2A.tc.description: Voltage regulator time constant (TC) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.

ExcIEEEDC2A.te.description: Exciter time constant, integration rate associated with exciter control (TE) (> 0). Typical value = 1,33.

ExcIEEEDC2A.vrmin.description: Minimum voltage regulator output (VRMIN) (< 0 and < ExcIEEEDC2A.vrmax). Typical value = -4,9.

ExcIEEEDC3A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type DC3A model. This model represents older systems, in particular those DC commutator exciters with non-continuously acting regulators that were commonly used before the development of the continuously acting varieties.  These systems respond at basically two different rates, depending upon the magnitude of voltage error. For small errors, adjustment is made periodically with a signal to a motor-operated rheostat. Larger errors cause resistors to be quickly shorted or inserted and a strong forcing signal applied to the exciter. Continuous motion of the motor-operated rheostat occurs for these larger error signals, even though it is bypassed by contactor action.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 5.3.

ExcIEEEDC3A.efd1.description: Exciter voltage at which exciter saturation is defined (EFD1) (> 0). Typical value = 3,375.

ExcIEEEDC3A.efd2.description: Exciter voltage at which exciter saturation is defined (EFD2) (> 0). Typical value = 3,15.

ExcIEEEDC3A.exclim.description: (exclim). IEEE standard is ambiguous about lower limit on exciter output. true = a lower limit of zero is applied to integrator output false = a lower limit of zero is not applied to integrator output. Typical value = true.

ExcIEEEDC3A.ke.description: Exciter constant related to self-excited field (KE). Typical value = 0,05.

ExcIEEEDC3A.kv.description: Fast raise/lower contact setting (KV) (> 0). Typical value = 0,05.

ExcIEEEDC3A.seefd1.description: Exciter saturation function value at the corresponding exciter voltage, EFD1 (SE[EFD1]) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,267.

ExcIEEEDC3A.seefd2.description: Exciter saturation function value at the corresponding exciter voltage, EFD2 (SE[EFD2]) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,068.

ExcIEEEDC3A.te.description: Exciter time constant, integration rate associated with exciter control (TE) (> 0). Typical value = 0,5.

ExcIEEEDC3A.vrmax.description: Maximum voltage regulator output (VRMAX) (> 0). Typical value = 1.

ExcIEEEDC3A.vrmin.description: Minimum voltage regulator output (VRMIN) (<= 0). Typical value = 0.

ExcIEEEDC4B.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type DC4B model. These excitation systems utilize a field-controlled DC commutator exciter with a continuously acting voltage regulator having supplies obtained from the generator or auxiliary bus.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 5.4.

ExcIEEEDC4B.uelin.description: UEL input (UELin). true = HV gate false = add to error signal. Typical value = true.

ExcIEEEDC4B.vrmax.description: Maximum voltage regulator output (VRMAX) (> ExcIEEEDC4B.vrmin). Typical value = 2,7.

ExcIEEEDC4B.vrmin.description: Minimum voltage regulator output (VRMIN) (<= 0 and < ExcIEEEDC4B.vrmax). Typical value = -0,9.

ExcIEEEST1A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type ST1A model. This model represents systems in which excitation power is supplied through a transformer from the generator terminals (or the unit’s auxiliary bus) and is regulated by a controlled rectifier.  The maximum exciter voltage available from such systems is directly related to the generator terminal voltage.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 7.1.

ExcIEEEST2A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type ST2A model. Some static systems use both current and voltage sources (generator terminal quantities) to comprise the power source.  The regulator controls the exciter output through controlled saturation of the power transformer components.  These compound-source rectifier excitation systems are designated type ST2A and are represented by ExcIEEEST2A.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 7.2.

ExcIEEEST3A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type ST3A model.  Some static systems utilize a field voltage control loop to linearize the exciter control characteristic. This also makes the output independent of supply source variations until supply limitations are reached.  These systems utilize a variety of controlled-rectifier designs: full thyristor complements or hybrid bridges in either series or shunt configurations. The power source can consist of only a potential source, either fed from the machine terminals or from internal windings. Some designs can have compound power sources utilizing both machine potential and current. These power sources are represented as phasor combinations of machine terminal current and voltage and are accommodated by suitable parameters in model type ST3A which is represented by ExcIEEEST3A.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 7.3.

ExcIEEEST4B.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type ST4B model. This model is a variation of the type ST3A model, with a proportional plus integral (PI) regulator block replacing the lag-lead regulator characteristic that is in the ST3A model. Both potential and compound source rectifier excitation systems are modelled.  The PI regulator blocks have non-windup limits that are represented. The voltage regulator of this model is typically implemented digitally.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 7.4.

The type ST5B excitation system is a variation of the type ST1A model, with alternative overexcitation and underexcitation inputs and additional limits. The block diagram in the IEEE 421.5 standard has input signal Vc and does not indicate the summation point with Vref. The implementation of the ExcIEEEST5B shall consider summation point with Vref. ExcIEEEST7B.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type ST7B model. This model is representative of static potential-source excitation systems. In this system, the AVR consists of a PI voltage regulator. A phase lead-lag filter in series allows the introduction of a derivative function, typically used with brushless excitation systems. In that case, the regulator is of the PID type. In addition, the terminal voltage channel includes a phase lead-lag filter.  The AVR includes the appropriate inputs on its reference for overexcitation limiter (OEL1), underexcitation limiter (UEL), stator current limiter (SCL), and current compensator (DROOP). All these limitations, when they work at voltage reference level, keep the PSS (VS signal from PSS) in operation. However, the UEL limitation can also be transferred to the high value (HV) gate acting on the output signal. In addition, the output signal passes through a low value (LV) gate for a ceiling overexcitation limiter (OEL2).
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 7.7.

OverexcLimIEEE.description:
The over excitation limiter model is intended to represent the significant features of OELs necessary for some large-scale system studies. It is the result of a pragmatic approach to obtain a model that can be widely applied with attainable data from generator owners. An attempt to include all variations in the functionality of OELs and duplicate how they interact with the rest of the excitation systems would likely result in a level of application insufficient for the studies for which they are intended.
Reference: IEEE OEL 421.5-2005, 9.

OverexcLimIEEE.ifdmax.description: OEL instantaneous field current limit (IFDMAX). Typical value = 1,5.

OverexcLimIEEE.itfpu.description: OEL timed field current limiter pickup level (ITFPU). Typical value = 1,05.

OverexcLimIEEE.kramp.description: OEL ramped limit rate (KRAMP). Unit = PU / s. Typical value = 10.

OverexcLim2.description: Different from LimIEEEOEL, LimOEL2 has a fixed pickup threshold and reduces the excitation set-point by means of a non-windup integral regulator. Irated is the rated machine excitation current (calculated from nameplate conditions: Vnom, Pnom, CosPhinom).

OverexcLim2.ifdlim.description: Limit value of rated field current (IFDLIM). Typical value = 1,05.

OverexcLim2.koi.description: Gain Over excitation limiter (KOI). Typical value = 0,1.

OverexcLim2.voimax.description: Maximum error signal (VOIMAX) (> OverexcLim2.voimin). Typical value = 0.

OverexcLim2.voimin.description: Minimum error signal (VOIMIN) (< OverexcLim2.voimax). Typical value = -9999.

OverexcLimX1.efd1.description: Low voltage point on the inverse time characteristic (EFD1). Typical value = 1,1.

OverexcLimX1.efd2.description: Mid voltage point on the inverse time characteristic (EFD2). Typical value = 1,2.

OverexcLimX1.efd3.description: High voltage point on the inverse time characteristic (EFD3). Typical value = 1,5.

OverexcLimX1.t2.description: Time to trip the exciter at the mid voltage point on the inverse time characteristic (TIME2) (>= 0). Typical value = 40.

OverexcLimX1.t3.description: Time to trip the exciter at the high voltage point on the inverse time characteristic (TIME3) (>= 0). Typical value = 15.

OverexcLimX2.description: Field voltage or current overexcitation limiter designed to protect the generator field of an AC machine with automatic excitation control from overheating due to prolonged overexcitation.

OverexcLimX2.efd1.description: Low voltage or current point on the inverse time characteristic (EFD1). Typical value = 1,1.

OverexcLimX2.efd2.description: Mid voltage or current point on the inverse time characteristic (EFD2). Typical value = 1,2.

OverexcLimX2.efd3.description: High voltage or current point on the inverse time characteristic (EFD3). Typical value = 1,5.

OverexcLimX2.efdrated.description: Rated field voltage if m = false or rated field current if m = true (EFDRATED). Typical value = 1,05.

OverexcLimX2.m.description: (m). true = IFD limiting false = EFD limiting.

PssIEEE1A.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type PSS1A power system stabilizer model. PSS1A is the generalized form of a PSS with a single input signal. 
Reference: IEEE 1A 421.5-2005, 8.1.

PssIEEE1A.a1.description: PSS signal conditioning frequency filter constant (A1). Typical value = 0,061.

PssIEEE1A.a2.description: PSS signal conditioning frequency filter constant (A2). Typical value = 0,0017.

InputSignalKind.rotorAngularFrequencyDev.description: Input signal is rotor or shaft angular frequency deviation.

InputSignalKind.busFrequency.description: Input signal is bus voltage fr<font color="#0f0f0f">equency.  This could be a terminal frequency or remote frequency.</font>

InputSignalKind.busFrequencyDeviation.description: Input signal is deviation of bus voltage frequ<font color="#0f0f0f">ency.  This could be a terminal frequency deviation or remote frequency deviation.</font>

InputSignalKind.generatorElectricalPower.description: Input signal is generator electrical power on rated S.

InputSignalKind.generatorAcceleratingPow.description: Input signal is generator accelerating power.

InputSignalKind.busVoltage.description: Input signal <font color="#0f0f0f">is bus voltage.  This could be a terminal voltage or remote voltage.</font>

InputSignalKind.busVoltageDerivative.description: Input signal is derivative of bus voltag<font color="#0f0f0f">e.  This could be a terminal voltage derivative or remote voltage derivative.</font>

InputSignalKind.branchCurrent.description: Input signal is amplitude of remote branch current.

InputSignalKind.fieldCurrent.description: Input signal is generator field current.

InputSignalKind.generatorMechanicalPower.description: Input signal is generator mechanical power.

PssIEEE2B.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type PSS2B power system stabilizer model. This stabilizer model is designed to represent a variety of dual-input stabilizers, which normally use combinations of power and speed or frequency to derive the stabilizing signal.
Reference: IEEE 2B 421.5-2005, 8.2.

PssIEEE2B.inputSignal2Type.description: Type of input signal #2 (generatorElectricalPower).  Typical value = generatorElectricalPower.

PssIEEE3B.description:
IEEE 421.5-2005 type PSS3B power system stabilizer model. The PSS model PSS3B has dual inputs of electrical power and rotor angular frequency deviation. The signals are used to derive an equivalent mechanical power signal.
This model has 2 input signals. They have the following fixed types (expressed in terms of InputSignalKind values): the first one is of rotorAngleFrequencyDeviation type and the second one is of generatorElectricalPower type.
Reference: IEEE 3B 421.5-2005, 8.3.

PssIEEE3B.vstmax.description: Stabilizer output maximum limit (Vstmax) (> PssIEEE3B.vstmin). Typical value = 0,1.

PssIEEE3B.vstmin.description: Stabilizer output minimum limit (Vstmin) (< PssIEEE3B.vstmax). Typical value = -0,1.

PssIEEE4B.description: IEEE 421.5-2005 type PSS4B power system stabilizer. The PSS4B model represents a structure based on multiple working frequency bands. Three separate bands, respectively dedicated to the low-, intermediate- and high-frequency modes of oscillations, are used in this delta omega (speed input) PSS. There is an error in the in IEEE 421.5-2005 PSS4B model: the Pe input should read –Pe. This implies that the input Pe needs to be multiplied by -1. Reference: IEEE 4B 421.5-2005, 8.4. Parameter details: This model has 2 input signals. They have the following fixed types (expressed in terms of InputSignalKind values): the first one is of rotorAngleFrequencyDeviation type and the second one is of generatorElectricalPower type.

PssIEEE4B.vimax.description: Intermediate band output maximum limit (VImax) (> PssIEEE4B.vimin). Typical value = 0,6.

PssIEEE4B.vimin.description: Intermediate band output minimum limit (VImin) (< PssIEEE4B.vimax). Typical value = -0,6.

PssIEEE4B.vlmax.description: Low band output maximum limit (VLmax) (> PssIEEE4B.vlmin). Typical value = 0,075.

PssIEEE4B.vlmin.description: Low band output minimum limit (VLmin) (< PssIEEE4B.vlmax). Typical value = -0,075.

PssIEEE4B.vstmax.description: PSS output maximum limit (VSTmax) (> PssIEEE4B.vstmin). Typical value = 0,15.

PssIEEE4B.vstmin.description: PSS output minimum limit (VSTmin) (< PssIEEE4B.vstmax). Typical value = -0,15.

Pss1.description: Italian PSS with three inputs (speed, frequency, power).

Pss1.kf.description: Frequency power input gain (KF). Typical value = 5.

Pss1.komega.description: Shaft speed power input gain (Komega). Typical value = 0.

Pss1.kpe.description: Electric power input gain (KPE). Typical value = 0,3.

Pss1.pmin.description: Minimum power PSS enabling (Pmin). Typical value = 0,25.

Pss1.t7.description: Lead/lag time constant (T7) (>= 0). If = 0, both blocks are bypassed. Typical value = 0.

Pss1.t9.description: Lead/lag time constant (T9) (>= 0). If = 0, both blocks are bypassed. Typical value = 0.

Pss1.tpe.description: Electric power filter time constant (TPE) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,05.

Pss1.vadat.description: Signal selector (VADAT). true = closed (generator power is greater than Pmin) false = open (Pe is smaller than Pmin). Typical value = true.

Pss1.vsmn.description: Stabilizer output maximum limit (VSMN). Typical value = -0,06.

Pss1.vsmx.description: Stabilizer output minimum limit (VSMX). Typical value = 0,06.

Pss1A.description: Single input power system stabilizer. It is a modified version in order to allow representation of various vendors' implementations on PSS type 1A.

Pss1A.inputSignalType.description: Type of input signal (rotorAngularFrequencyDeviation, busFrequencyDeviation, generatorElectricalPower, generatorAcceleratingPower, busVoltage, or busVoltageDerivative).

Pss1A.kd.description: Selector (Kd). true = e-sTdelay used false = e-sTdelay not used.

Pss2B.description: Modified IEEE PSS2B.  Extra lead/lag (or rate) block added at end (up to 4 lead/lags total).

Pss2B.ks3.description: Gain on signal #2 input before ramp-tracking filter (Ks3). Typical value = 1.

Pss2B.ks4.description: Gain on signal #2 input after ramp-tracking filter (Ks4). Typical value = 1.

Pss2B.m.description: Denominator order of ramp tracking filter (m). Typical value = 5.

Pss2B.n.description: Order of ramp tracking filter (n). Typical value = 1.

Pss2B.t6.description: Time constant on signal #1 (T6) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.

Pss2B.t7.description: Time constant on signal #2 (T7) (>= 0). Typical value = 2.

Pss2B.t8.description: Lead of ramp tracking filter (T8) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,2.

Pss2B.t9.description: Lag of ramp tracking filter (T9) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,1.

Pss2B.tw1.description: First washout on signal #1 (Tw1) (>= 0). Typical value = 2.

Pss2B.tw2.description: Second washout on signal #1 (Tw2) (>= 0). Typical value = 2.

Pss2B.tw3.description: First washout on signal #2 (Tw3) (>= 0). Typical value = 2.

Pss2B.tw4.description: Second washout on signal #2 (Tw4) (>= 0). Typical value = 0.

Pss2B.vsi1max.description: Input signal #1 maximum limit (Vsi1max) (> Pss2B.vsi1min). Typical value = 2.

Pss2B.vsi1min.description: Input signal #1 minimum limit (Vsi1min) (< Pss2B.vsi1max). Typical value = -2.

Pss2B.vsi2max.description: Input signal #2 maximum limit (Vsi2max) (> Pss2B.vsi2min). Typical value = 2.

Pss2B.vsi2min.description: Input signal #2 minimum limit (Vsi2min) (< Pss2B.vsi2max). Typical value = -2.

Pss2B.vstmax.description: Stabilizer output maximum limit (Vstmax) (> Pss2B.vstmin). Typical value = 0,1.

Pss2B.vstmin.description: Stabilizer output minimum limit (Vstmin) (< Pss2B.vstmax). Typical value = -0,1.

Pss2ST.inputSignal1Type.description: Type of input signal #1 (rotorAngularFrequencyDeviation, busFrequencyDeviation, generatorElectricalPower, generatorAcceleratingPower, busVoltage, or busVoltageDerivative - shall be different than Pss2ST.inputSignal2Type).  Typical value = rotorAngularFrequencyDeviation.

Pss2ST.inputSignal2Type.description: Type of input signal #2 (rotorAngularFrequencyDeviation, busFrequencyDeviation, generatorElectricalPower, generatorAcceleratingPower, busVoltage, or busVoltageDerivative - shall be different than Pss2ST.inputSignal1Type).  Typical value = busVoltageDerivative.

Pss5.ctw2.description: Selector for second washout enabling (CTW2). true = second washout filter is bypassed false = second washout filter in use. Typical value = true.

Pss5.isfreq.description: Selector for frequency/shaft speed input (isFreq). true = speed (same meaning as InputSignaKind.rotorSpeed) false = frequency (same meaning as InputSignalKind.busFrequency). Typical value = true (same meaning as InputSignalKind.rotorSpeed).

Pss5.kf.description: Frequency/shaft speed input gain (KF). Typical value = 5.

Pss5.kpe.description: Electric power input gain (KPE). Typical value = 0,3.

Pss5.pmin.description: Minimum power PSS enabling (Pmin). Typical value = 0,25.

Pss5.tl2.description: Lead/lag time constant (TL2) (>= 0). If = 0, both blocks are bypassed. Typical value = 0.

Pss5.tl4.description: Lead/lag time constant (T<sub>L4</sub>) (>= 0).  If = 0, both blocks are bypassed.  Typical value = 0.

Pss5.tpe.description: Electric power filter time constant (TPE) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,05.

Pss5.vadat.description: Signal selector (VadAtt). true = closed (generator power is greater than Pmin) false = open (Pe is smaller than Pmin). Typical value = true.

Pss5.vsmn.description: Stabilizer output maximum limit (VSMN). Typical value = -0,1.

Pss5.vsmx.description: Stabilizer output minimum limit (VSMX). Typical value = 0,1.

PssELIN2.description: Power system stabilizer typically associated with ExcELIN2 (though PssIEEE2B or Pss2B can also be used).

PssPTIST1.dtc.description: Time step related to activation of controls (deltatc) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,025.

PssPTIST1.dtf.description: Time step frequency calculation (deltatf) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,025.

PssPTIST1.dtp.description: Time step active power calculation (deltatp) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,0125.

PssPTIST3.athres.description: Threshold value above which output averaging will be bypassed (Athres). Typical value = 0,005.

PssPTIST3.dtc.description: Time step related to activation of controls (deltatc) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,025 (0,03 for 50 Hz).

PssPTIST3.dtf.description: Time step frequency calculation (deltatf) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,025 (0,03 for 50 Hz).

PssPTIST3.dtp.description: Time step active power calculation (deltatp) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,0125 (0,015 for 50 Hz).

PssPTIST3.isw.description: Digital/analogue output switch (Isw). true = produce analogue output false = convert to digital output, using tap selection table.

PssPTIST3.nav.description: Number of control outputs to average (NAV) (1 <= NAV <= 16). Typical value = 4.

PssPTIST3.ncl.description: Number of counts at limit to active limit function (NCL) (> 0).

PssPTIST3.ncr.description: Number of counts until reset after limit function is triggered (NCR).

PssRQB.description: Power system stabilizer type RQB. This power system stabilizer is intended to be used together with excitation system type ExcRQB, which is primarily used in nuclear or thermal generating units.

PssRQB.ki3.description: Electrical power input gain (Ki3). Typical value = -11,45.

PssRQB.ki4.description: Mechanical power input gain (Ki4). Typical value = 11,86.

PssRQB.t4f.description: Lead lag time constant (T4F) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,045.

PssSH.description:
Siemens<sup>TM</sup> “H infinity” power system stabilizer with generator electrical power input.
[Footnote: Siemens "H infinity" power system stabilizers are an example of suitable products available commercially. This information is given for the convenience of users of this document and does not constitute an endorsement by IEC of these products.]

PssSH.vsmax.description: Output maximum limit (Vsmax) (> PssSH.vsmin). Typical value = 0,1.

PssSH.vsmin.description: Output minimum limit (Vsmin) (< PssSH.vsmax). Typical value = -0,1.

PssSK.vsmax.description: Stabilizer output maximum limit (VSMAX) (> PssSK.vsmin). Typical value = 0,4.

PssSK.vsmin.description: Stabilizer output minimum limit (VSMIN) (< PssSK.vsmax). Typical value = -0.4.

PssSTAB2A.description:
Power system stabilizer part of an ABB excitation system.
[Footnote: ABB excitation systems are an example of suitable products available commercially. This information is given for the convenience of users of this document and does not constitute an endorsement by IEC of these products.]

PssWECC.description: Dual input power system stabilizer, based on IEEE type 2, with modified output limiter defined by WECC (Western Electricity Coordinating Council, USA).

PssWECC.inputSignal1Type.description: Type of input signal #1 (rotorAngularFrequencyDeviation, busFrequencyDeviation, generatorElectricalPower, generatorAcceleratingPower, busVoltage, or busVoltageDerivative - shall be different than PssWECC.inputSignal2Type).  Typical value = rotorAngularFrequencyDeviation.

PssWECC.inputSignal2Type.description: Type of input signal #2 (rotorAngularFrequencyDeviation, busFrequencyDeviation, generatorElectricalPower, generatorAcceleratingPower, busVoltage, busVoltageDerivative - shall be different than PssWECC.inputSignal1Type).  Typical value = busVoltageDerivative.

PssWECC.t1.description: Input signal 1 transducer time constant (T1) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,037.

PssWECC.t2.description: Input signal 2 transducer time constant (T2) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,0.

PssWECC.t3.description: Stabilizer washout time constant (T3) (>= 0). Typical value = 9,5.

PssWECC.t4.description: Stabilizer washout time lag constant (T4) (>= 0). Typical value = 9,5.

PssWECC.vcl.description: Minimum value for voltage compensator output (VCL). Typical value = 0.

PssWECC.vcu.description: Maximum value for voltage compensator output (VCU). Typical value = 0.

PssWECC.vsmax.description: Maximum output signal (Vsmax) (> PssWECC.vsmin). Typical value = 0,05.

PssWECC.vsmin.description: Minimum output signal (Vsmin) (< PssWECC.vsmax). Typical value = -0,05.

DiscExcContIEEEDEC1A.description:
IEEE type DEC1A discontinuous excitation control model that boosts generator excitation to a level higher than that demanded by the voltage regulator and stabilizer immediately following a system fault.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 12.2.

DiscExcContIEEEDEC1A.ketl.description: Terminal voltage limiter gain (KETL). Typical value = 47.

DiscExcContIEEEDEC1A.tan.description: Discontinuous controller time constant (TAN) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,08.

DiscExcContIEEEDEC1A.tw5.description: DEC washout time constant (TW5) (>= 0). Typical value = 5.

DiscExcContIEEEDEC1A.vtc.description: Terminal voltage level reference (VTC). Typical value = 0,95.

DiscExcContIEEEDEC2A.description:
IEEE type DEC2A model for discontinuous excitation control. This system provides transient excitation boosting via an open-loop control as initiated by a trigger signal generated remotely.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005 12.3.

DiscExcContIEEEDEC3A.description:
IEEE type DEC3A model. In some systems, the stabilizer output is disconnected from the regulator immediately following a severe fault to prevent the stabilizer from competing with action of voltage regulator during the first swing.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005 12.4.

PFVArType1IEEEPFController.description:
IEEE PF controller type 1 which operates by moving the voltage reference directly.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 11.2.

PFVArType1IEEEPFController.ovex.description: Overexcitation Flag (OVEX) true = overexcited false = underexcited.

PFVArType1IEEEPFController.tpfc.description: PF controller time delay (TPFC) (>= 0). Typical value = 5.

PFVArType1IEEEPFController.vitmin.description: Minimum machine terminal current needed to enable pf/var controller (VITMIN).

PFVArType1IEEEPFController.vvtmax.description: Maximum machine terminal voltage needed for pf/var controller to be enabled (VVTMAX) (> PFVArType1IEEEPFController.vvtmin).

PFVArType1IEEEPFController.vvtmin.description: Minimum machine terminal voltage needed to enable pf/var controller (VVTMIN) (< PFVArType1IEEEPFController.vvtmax).

PFVArType1IEEEVArController.description:
IEEE VAR controller type 1 which operates by moving the voltage reference directly.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 11.3.

PFVArType1IEEEVArController.tvarc.description: Var controller time delay (TVARC) (>= 0). Typical value = 5.

PFVArType1IEEEVArController.vvtmax.description: Maximum machine terminal voltage needed for pf/VAr controller to be enabled (VVTMAX) (> PVFArType1IEEEVArController.vvtmin).

PFVArType1IEEEVArController.vvtmin.description: Minimum machine terminal voltage needed to enable pf/var controller (VVTMIN) (< PVFArType1IEEEVArController.vvtmax).

VAdjIEEE.description:
IEEE voltage adjuster which is used to represent the voltage adjuster in either a power factor or VAr control system.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 11.1.

VAdjIEEE.adjslew.description: Rate at which output of adjuster changes (ADJ_SLEW). Unit = s / PU. Typical value = 300.

VAdjIEEE.taoff.description: Time that adjuster pulses are off (TAOFF) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,5.

VAdjIEEE.taon.description: Time that adjuster pulses are on (TAON) (>= 0). Typical value = 0,1.

VAdjIEEE.vadjf.description: Set high to provide a continuous raise or lower (VADJF).

VAdjIEEE.vadjmax.description: Maximum output of the adjuster (VADJMAX) (> VAdjIEEE.vadjmin). Typical value = 1,1.

VAdjIEEE.vadjmin.description: Minimum output of the adjuster (VADJMIN) (< VAdjIEEE.vadjmax). Typical value = 0,9.

PFVArType2IEEEPFController.description:
IEEE PF controller type 2 which is a summing point type controller making up the outside loop of a two-loop system. This controller is implemented as a slow PI type controller. The voltage regulator forms the inner loop and is implemented as a fast controller.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 11.4.

PFVArType2IEEEPFController.exlon.description: Overexcitation or under excitation flag (EXLON) true = 1 (not in the overexcitation or underexcitation state, integral action is active) false = 0 (in the overexcitation or underexcitation state, so integral action is disabled to allow the limiter to play its role).

PFVArType2IEEEPFController.ki.description: Integral gain of the pf controller (KI). Typical value = 1.

PFVArType2IEEEPFController.kp.description: Proportional gain of the pf controller (KP). Typical value = 1.

PFVArType2IEEEPFController.vclmt.description: Maximum output of the pf controller (VCLMT). Typical value = 0,1.

PFVArType2IEEEVArController.description:
IEEE VAR controller type 2 which is a summing point type controller. It makes up the outside loop of a two-loop system. This controller is implemented as a slow PI type controller, and the voltage regulator forms the inner loop and is implemented as a fast controller.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 11.5.

PFVArType2IEEEVArController.exlon.description: Overexcitation or under excitation flag (EXLON) true = 1 (not in the overexcitation or underexcitation state, integral action is active) false = 0 (in the overexcitation or underexcitation state, so integral action is disabled to allow the limiter to play its role).

PFVArType2IEEEVArController.ki.description: Integral gain of the pf controller (KI).

PFVArType2IEEEVArController.kp.description: Proportional gain of the pf controller (KP).

PFVArType2IEEEVArController.vclmt.description: Maximum output of the pf controller (VCLMT).

PFVArType2Common1.description:
Power factor / reactive power regulator. This model represents the power factor or reactive power controller such as the Basler SCP-250. The controller measures power factor or reactive power (PU on generator rated power) and compares it with the operator's set point.
[Footnote: Basler SCP-250 is an example of a suitable product available commercially. This information is given for the convenience of users of this document and does not constitute an endorsement by IEC of this product.]

PFVArType2Common1.j.description: Selector (J). true = control mode for reactive power false = control mode for power factor.

PFVArType2Common1.ref.description: Reference value of reactive power or power factor (Ref). The reference value is initialised by this model. This initialisation can override the value exchanged by this attribute to represent a plant operator's change of the reference setting.

VCompIEEEType1.description:
Terminal voltage transducer and load compensator as defined in IEEE 421.5-2005, 4. This model is common to all excitation system models described in the IEEE Standard. Parameter details:
  1. If Rc and Xc are set to zero, the load compensation is not employed and the behaviour is as a simple sensing circuit.
  1. If all parameters (Rc, Xc and Tr) are set to zero, the standard model VCompIEEEType1 is bypassed.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005 4.

VCompIEEEType1.rc.description: Resistive component of compensation of a generator (Rc) (>= 0).

VCompIEEEType1.tr.description: Time constant which is used for the combined voltage sensing and compensation signal (Tr) (>= 0).

VCompIEEEType1.xc.description: Reactive component of compensation of a generator (Xc) (>= 0).

VCompIEEEType2.description:
Terminal voltage transducer and load compensator as defined in IEEE 421.5-2005, 4. This model is designed to cover the following types of compensation:
  • reactive droop;
  • transformer-drop or line-drop compensation;
  • reactive differential compensation known also as cross-current compensation.
Reference: IEEE 421.5-2005, 4.

VCompIEEEType2.tr.description: Time constant which is used for the combined voltage sensing and compensation signal (Tr) (>= 0).

GenICompensationForGenJ.description: Resistive and reactive components of compensation for generator associated with IEEE type 2 voltage compensator for current flow out of another generator in the interconnection.

GenICompensationForGenJ.SynchronousMachi.description: Standard synchronous machine out of which current flow is being compensated for.

GenICompensationForGenJ.VcompIEEEType2.description: The standard IEEE type 2 voltage compensator of this compensation.

GenICompensationForGenJ.rcij.description: Resistive component of compensation of generator associated with this IEEE type 2 voltage compensator for current flow out of another generator (Rcij).

GenICompensationForGenJ.xcij.description: Reactive component of compensation of generator associated with this IEEE type 2 voltage compensator for current flow out of another generator (Xcij).

WindAeroConstIEC.description:
Constant aerodynamic torque model which assumes that the aerodynamic torque is constant.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.1.1.

WindAeroOneDimIEC.ka.description: Aerodynamic gain (ka). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindAeroOneDimIEC.thetaomega.description: Initial pitch angle (thetaomega0). It is a case-dependent parameter.

WindAeroTwoDimIEC.dpomega.description: Partial derivative of aerodynamic power with respect to changes in WTR speed (dpomega). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindAeroTwoDimIEC.dptheta.description: Partial derivative of aerodynamic power with respect to changes in pitch angle (dptheta). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindAeroTwoDimIEC.dpv1.description: Partial derivative (dpv1). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindAeroTwoDimIEC.omegazero.description: Rotor speed if the wind turbine is not derated (omega0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindAeroTwoDimIEC.pavail.description: Available aerodynamic power (pavail). It is a case-dependent parameter.

WindAeroTwoDimIEC.thetav2.description: Blade angle at twice rated wind speed (thetav2). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindAeroTwoDimIEC.thetazero.description: Pitch angle if the wind turbine is not derated (theta0). It is a case-dependent parameter.

WindContCurrLimIEC.description:
Current limitation model.  The current limitation model combines the physical limits and the control limits.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.8.

WindContCurrLimIEC.imax.description: Maximum continuous current at the wind turbine terminals (imax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContCurrLimIEC.imaxdip.description: Maximum current during voltage dip at the wind turbine terminals (imaxdip). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContCurrLimIEC.kpqu.description: Partial derivative of reactive current limit (Kpqu) versus voltage. It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContCurrLimIEC.mdfslim.description: Limitation of type 3 stator current (MDFSLim). MDFSLim = 1 for wind turbines type 4. It is a type-dependent parameter. false= total current limitation (0 in the IEC model) true=stator current limitation (1 in the IEC model).

WindContCurrLimIEC.mqpri.description: Prioritisation of Q control during UVRT (Mqpri). It is a project-dependent parameter. true = reactive power priority (1 in the IEC model) false = active power priority (0 in the IEC model).

WindContCurrLimIEC.tufiltcl.description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltcl) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContCurrLimIEC.upqumax.description: Wind turbine voltage in the operation point where zero reactive current can be delivered (upqumax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.description:
Pitch angle control model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.2.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.dthetamax.description: Maximum pitch positive ramp rate (dthetamax) (> WindContPitchAngleIEC.dthetamin). It is a type-dependent parameter. Unit = degrees / s.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.dthetamin.description: Maximum pitch negative ramp rate (dthetamin) (< WindContPitchAngleIEC.dthetamax). It is a type-dependent parameter. Unit = degrees / s.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.kic.description: Power PI controller integration gain (KIc). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.kiomega.description: Speed PI controller integration gain (KIomega). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.kpc.description: Power PI controller proportional gain (KPc). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.kpomega.description: Speed PI controller proportional gain (KPomega). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.kpx.description: Pitch cross coupling gain (KPX). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.thetamax.description: Maximum pitch angle (thetamax) (> WindContPitchAngleIEC.thetamin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.thetamin.description: Minimum pitch angle (thetamin) (< WindContPitchAngleIEC.thetamax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPitchAngleIEC.ttheta.description: Pitch time constant (ttheta) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.description:
P control model type 3.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.4.

WindContPType3IEC.dpmax.description: Maximum wind turbine power ramp rate (dpmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.dprefmax.description: Maximum ramp rate of wind turbine reference power (dprefmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.dprefmin.description: Minimum ramp rate of wind turbine reference power (dprefmin). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.dthetamax.description: Ramp limitation of torque, required in some grid codes (dtmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.dthetamaxuvrt.description: Limitation of torque rise rate during UVRT (dthetamaxUVRT). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.kdtd.description: Gain for active drive train damping (KDTD). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.kip.description: PI controller integration parameter (KIp). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.kpp.description: PI controller proportional gain (KPp). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.mpuvrt.description: Enable UVRT power control mode (MpUVRT). It is a project-dependent parameter. true = voltage control (1 in the IEC model) false = reactive power control (0 in the IEC model).

WindContPType3IEC.omegadtd.description: Active drive train damping frequency (omegaDTD). It can be calculated from two mass model parameters. It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.omegaoffset.description: Offset to reference value that limits controller action during rotor speed changes (omegaoffset). It is a case-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.pdtdmax.description: Maximum active drive train damping power (pDTDmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.tdvs.description: Time delay after deep voltage sags (TDVS) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.thetaemin.description: Minimum electrical generator torque (temin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.thetauscale.description: Voltage scaling factor of reset-torque (tuscale). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.tomegafiltp3.description: Filter time constant for generator speed measurement (Tomegafiltp3) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.tomegaref.description: Time constant in speed reference filter (Tomega,ref) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.tpfiltp3.description: Filter time constant for power measurement (Tpfiltp3) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.tpord.description: Time constant in power order lag (Tpord). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.tufiltp3.description: Filter time constant for voltage measurement (Tufiltp3) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.udvs.description: Voltage limit for hold UVRT status after deep voltage sags (uDVS). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.updip.description: Voltage dip threshold for P-control (uPdip). Part of turbine control, often different (e.g 0.8) from converter thresholds. It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType3IEC.zeta.description: Coefficient for active drive train damping (zeta). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType4aIEC.description:
P control model type 4A.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.5.

WindContPType4aIEC.dpmaxp4a.description: Maximum wind turbine power ramp rate (dpmaxp4A). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType4aIEC.tpordp4a.description: Time constant in power order lag (Tpordp4A) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType4aIEC.tufiltp4a.description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltp4A) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType4bIEC.description:
P control model type 4B.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.6.

WindContPType4bIEC.dpmaxp4b.description: Maximum wind turbine power ramp rate (dpmaxp4B). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContPType4bIEC.tpaero.description: Time constant in aerodynamic power response (Tpaero) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType4bIEC.tpordp4b.description: Time constant in power order lag (Tpordp4B) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContPType4bIEC.tufiltp4b.description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltp4B) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.iqh1.description: Maximum reactive current injection during dip (iqh1). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.iqmax.description: Maximum reactive current injection (iqmax) (> WindContQIEC.iqmin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.iqmin.description: Minimum reactive current injection (iqmin) (< WindContQIEC.iqmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.iqpost.description: Post fault reactive current injection (iqpost). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.kiq.description: Reactive power PI controller integration gain (KI,q). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.kiu.description: Voltage PI controller integration gain (KI,u). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.kpq.description: Reactive power PI controller proportional gain (KP,q). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.kpu.description: Voltage PI controller proportional gain (KP,u). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.kqv.description: Voltage scaling factor for UVRT current (Kqv). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.rdroop.description: Resistive component of voltage drop impedance (rdroop) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.tpfiltq.description: Power measurement filter time constant (Tpfiltq) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.tpost.description: Length of time period where post fault reactive power is injected (Tpost) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.tqord.description: Time constant in reactive power order lag (Tqord) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.tufiltq.description: Voltage measurement filter time constant (Tufiltq) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.udb1.description: Voltage deadband lower limit (udb1). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.udb2.description: Voltage deadband upper limit (udb2). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.umax.description: Maximum voltage in voltage PI controller integral term (umax) (> WindContQIEC.umin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.umin.description: Minimum voltage in voltage PI controller integral term (umin) (< WindContQIEC.umax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.uqdip.description: Voltage threshold for UVRT detection in Q control (uqdip). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.uref0.description: User-defined bias in voltage reference (uref0). It is a case-dependent parameter.

WindQcontrolModeKind.openLoopReactivePow.description: Open loop reactive power control (only used with closed loop at plant level) (MqG equals 2).

WindContQIEC.windQcontrolModesType.description: Types of general wind turbine Q control modes (MqG). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindUVRTQcontrolModeKind.mode1.description: Reactive current injection controlled as the pre-fault value plus an additional voltage dependent reactive current injection (MqUVRT equals 1).

WindUVRTQcontrolModeKind.mode2.description: Reactive current injection controlled as the pre-fault value plus an additional voltage-dependent reactive current injection during fault, and as the pre-fault value plus an additional constant reactive current injection post fault (MqUVRT equals 2).

WindContQIEC.windUVRTQcontrolModesType.description: Types of UVRT Q control modes (MqUVRT). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContQIEC.xdroop.description: Inductive component of voltage drop impedance (xdroop) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindContQLimIEC.description:
Constant Q limitation model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.9.

WindContQLimIEC.qmax.description: Maximum reactive power (qmax) (> WindContQLimIEC.qmin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQLimIEC.qmin.description: Minimum reactive power (qmin) (< WindContQLimIEC.qmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQPQULimIEC.description:
QP and QU limitation model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.10.

WindContQPQULimIEC.tpfiltql.description: Power measurement filter time constant for Q capacity (Tpfiltql) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContQPQULimIEC.tufiltql.description: Voltage measurement filter time constant for Q capacity (Tufiltql) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.description:
Rotor resistance control model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.3.

WindContRotorRIEC.kirr.description: Integral gain in rotor resistance PI controller (KIrr). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.komegafilt.description: Filter gain for generator speed measurement (Komegafilt). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.kpfilt.description: Filter gain for power measurement (Kpfilt). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.kprr.description: Proportional gain in rotor resistance PI controller (KPrr). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.rmax.description: Maximum rotor resistance (rmax) (> WindContRotorRIEC.rmin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.rmin.description: Minimum rotor resistance (rmin) (< WindContRotorRIEC.rmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.tomegafiltrr.description: Filter time constant for generator speed measurement (Tomegafiltrr) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindContRotorRIEC.tpfiltrr.description: Filter time constant for power measurement (Tpfiltrr) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.description: Look up table for the purpose of wind standard models.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindContCurrLimI.description: The current control limitation model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindContPType3IE.description: The P control type 3 model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindContQPQULimI.description: The QP and QU limitation model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindContRotorRIE.description: The rotor resistance control model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindGenType3bIEC.description: The generator type 3B model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindPitchContPow.description: The pitch control power model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindPlantFreqPco.description: The frequency and active power wind plant control model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindPlantReactiv.description: The voltage and reactive power wind plant control model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.WindProtectionIE.description: The grid protection model with which this wind dynamics lookup table is associated.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.input.description: Input value (x) for the lookup table function.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.prr.description: Power versus speed change (negative slip) lookup table (p<sub>rr</sub>(deltaomega)). It is used for the rotor resistance control model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.3.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.omegap.description: Power vs. speed lookup table (omega(p)). It is used for the P control model type 3, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.4.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.ipmax.description: Lookup table for voltage dependency of active current limits (i<sub>pmax</sub>(u<sub>WT</sub>)). It is used for the current limitation model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.8.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.iqmax.description: Lookup table for voltage dependency of reactive current limits (i<sub>qmax</sub>(u<sub>WT</sub>)). It is used for the current limitation model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.8.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.pwp.description: Power vs. frequency lookup table (p<sub>WPbias</sub>(f)). It is used for the wind power plant frequency and active power control model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, Annex D.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.tcwdu.description: Crowbar duration versus voltage variation look-up table (T<sub>CW</sub>(du)). It is a case-dependent parameter. It is used for the type 3B generator set model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.3.3.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.tduwt.description: Lookup table to determine the duration of the power reduction after a voltage dip, depending on the size of the voltage dip (T<sub>d</sub>(u<sub>WT</sub>)). It is a type-dependent parameter. It is used for the pitch control power model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.1.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.qmaxp.description: Lookup table for active power dependency of reactive power maximum limit (q<sub>maxp</sub>(p)). It is used for the QP and QU limitation model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.10.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.qminp.description: Lookup table for active power dependency of reactive power minimum limit (q<sub>minp</sub>(p)). It is used for the QP and QU limitation model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.10.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.qmaxu.description: Lookup table for voltage dependency of reactive power maximum limit (q<sub>maxu</sub>(p)). It is used for the QP and QU limitation model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.10.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.qminu.description: Lookup table for voltage dependency of reactive power minimum limit (q<sub>minu</sub>(p)). It is used for the QP and QU limitation model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.10.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.tuover.description: Disconnection time versus over-voltage lookup table (T<sub>uover</sub>(u<sub>WT</sub>)). It is used for the grid protection model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.6.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.tuunder.description: Disconnection time versus under-voltage lookup table (T<sub>uunder</sub>(u<sub>WT</sub>)). It is used for the grid protection model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.6.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.tfover.description: Disconnection time versus over-frequency lookup table (T<sub>fover</sub>(f<sub>WT</sub>)). It is used for the grid protection model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.6.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.tfunder.description: Disconnection time versus under-frequency lookup table (T<sub>funder</sub>(f<sub>WT</sub>)). It is used for the grid protection model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.6.

WindLookupTableFunctionKind.qwp.description: Look up table for the UQ static mode (q<sub>WP</sub>(u<sub>err</sub>)). It is used for the voltage and reactive power control model, IEC 61400-27-1:2015, Annex D.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.lookupTableFunct.description: Type of the lookup table function.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.output.description: Output value (y) for the lookup table function.

WindDynamicsLookupTable.sequence.description: Sequence numbers of the pairs of the input (x) and the output (y) of the lookup table function.

WindGenTurbineType1aIEC.description:
Wind turbine IEC type 1A.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.5.2.2.

WindGenTurbineType1aIEC.WindAeroConstIEC.description: Wind aerodynamic model associated with this wind turbine type 1A model.

WindTurbineType1or2IEC.WindMechIEC.description: Wind mechanical model associated with this wind generator type 1 or type 2 model.

WindTurbineType1or2IEC.WindProtectionIEC.description: Wind turbune protection model associated with this wind generator type 1 or type 2 model.

WindGenTurbineType1bIEC.description:
Wind turbine IEC type 1B.

Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.5.2.3.

WindGenTurbineType1bIEC.WindPitchContPow.description: Pitch control power model associated with this wind turbine type 1B model.

WindGenTurbineType2IEC.description:
Wind turbine IEC type 2.

Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.5.3.

WindGenTurbineType2IEC.WindContRotorRIEC.description: Wind control rotor resistance model associated with wind turbine type 2 model.

WindGenTurbineType2IEC.WindPitchContPowe.description: Pitch control power model associated with this wind turbine type 2 model.

WindGenType3aIEC.description:
IEC type 3A generator set model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.3.2.

WindGenType3IEC.dipmax.description: Maximum active current ramp rate (dipmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindGenType3IEC.diqmax.description: Maximum reactive current ramp rate (diqmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindGenType3IEC.xs.description: Electromagnetic transient reactance (xS). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindGenType3aIEC.kpc.description: Current PI controller proportional gain (KPc). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindGenType3aIEC.tic.description: Current PI controller integration time constant (TIc) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindGenType3bIEC.description:
IEC type 3B generator set model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.3.3.

WindGenType3bIEC.mwtcwp.description: Crowbar control mode (MWTcwp). It is a case-dependent parameter. true = 1 in the IEC model false = 0 in the IEC model.

WindGenType3bIEC.tg.description: Current generation time constant (Tg) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindGenType3bIEC.two.description: Time constant for crowbar washout filter (Two) (>= 0). It is a case-dependent parameter.

WindGenType4IEC.description:
IEC type 4 generator set model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.3.4.

WindGenType4IEC.dipmax.description: Maximum active current ramp rate (dipmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindGenType4IEC.diqmax.description: Maximum reactive current ramp rate (diqmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindGenType4IEC.diqmin.description: Minimum reactive current ramp rate (diqmin). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindGenType4IEC.tg.description: Time constant (Tg) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindMechIEC.cdrt.description: Drive train damping (cdrt). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindMechIEC.hgen.description: Inertia constant of generator (Hgen) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindMechIEC.hwtr.description: Inertia constant of wind turbine rotor (HWTR) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindMechIEC.kdrt.description: Drive train stiffness (kdrt). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.description:
Pitch control power model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, 5.6.5.1.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.dpmax.description: Rate limit for increasing power (dpmax) (> WindPitchContPowerIEC.dpmin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.dpmin.description: Rate limit for decreasing power (dpmin) (< WindPitchContPowerIEC.dpmax). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.pmin.description: Minimum power setting (pmin). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.pset.description: If pinit < pset then power will be ramped down to pmin. It is (pset) in the IEC 61400-27-1:2015. It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.t1.description: Lag time constant (T1) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.tr.description: Voltage measurement time constant (Tr) (>= 0). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPitchContPowerIEC.uuvrt.description: Dip detection threshold (uUVRT). It is a type-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.description:
Frequency and active power controller model.
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, Annex D.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dprefmax.description: Maximum ramp rate of pWTref request from the plant controller to the wind turbines (dprefmax) (> WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dprefmin). It is a case-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dprefmin.description: Minimum (negative) ramp rate of pWTref request from the plant controller to the wind turbines (dprefmin) (< WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dprefmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dpwprefmax.description: Maximum positive ramp rate for wind plant power reference (dpWPrefmax) (> WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dpwprefmin). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dpwprefmin.description: Maximum negative ramp rate for wind plant power reference (dpWPrefmin) (< WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.dpwprefmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.kiwpp.description: Plant P controller integral gain (KIWPp). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.kiwppmax.description: Maximum PI integrator term (KIWPpmax) (> WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.kiwppmin). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.kiwppmin.description: Minimum PI integrator term (KIWPpmin) (< WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.kiwppmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.kpwpp.description: Plant P controller proportional gain (KPWPp). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.kwppref.description: Power reference gain (KWPpref). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.prefmax.description: Maximum pWTref request from the plant controller to the wind turbines (prefmax) (> WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.prefmin). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.prefmin.description: Minimum pWTref request from the plant controller to the wind turbines (prefmin) (< WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.prefmax). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.tpft.description: Lead time constant in reference value transfer function (Tpft) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.tpfv.description: Lag time constant in reference value transfer function (Tpfv) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.twpffiltp.description: Filter time constant for frequency measurement (TWPffiltp) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantFreqPcontrolIEC.twppfiltp.description: Filter time constant for active power measurement (TWPpfiltp) (>= 0). It is a project-dependent parameter.

WindPlantIEC.description:
Simplified IEC type plant level model. 
Reference: IEC 61400-27-1:2015, Annex D.
